spec: agent-core.ai-docs/v1
namespace: "Application\\Orchestrator"
fqcn: "Ineersa\\AgentCore\\Application\\Orchestrator"
updatedAt: 2026-04-22
description: Top-level orchestrators — AgentRunner is the public API facade; RunOrchestrator is the central CQRS processor handling all bus messages.
files[13]{file,type,summary}:
  AdvanceRunHandler.php,readonly final class,The AdvanceRunHandler applies turn-start mailbox policy and prepares the next LLM execution turn when the run can continue.
  AgentRunner.php,final class,"The AgentRunner class orchestrates the lifecycle of agent execution runs by translating high-level inputs into discrete, idempotent steps. It manages state transitions for starting, continuing, steering, and canceling runs while ensuring reliable message dispatch via a command bus."
  ApplyCommandHandler.php,readonly final class,The ApplyCommandHandler validates and maps incoming commands into durable command-mailbox transitions.
  CommandMailboxPolicy.php,readonly final class,Applies queued command mailbox policies at turn boundaries and validates cancellation and continue admissibility rules.
  HandlerResult.php,readonly final class,The HandlerResult captures the durable transition and post-commit work emitted by a run message handler.
  LlmStepResultHandler.php,readonly final class,"The LlmStepResultHandler applies LLM step outcomes, including stop-boundary command policy and tool-call fanout preparation."
  RunCommit.php,readonly final class,"Owns the durable run-commit lifecycle from compare-and-swap persistence through projection, replay rebuild, effects dispatch, hooks, and observability updates."
  RunMessageHandler.php,interface,The RunMessageHandler maps a bus message and current run state into a declarative transition result consumed by the message processor.
  RunMessageProcessor.php,readonly final class,The RunMessageProcessor executes the shared lock/idempotency/load/commit pipeline around dedicated run message handlers.
  RunMessageStateTools.php,readonly final class,The RunMessageStateTools provide shared immutable state-copy and payload-hydration helpers for run message handlers.
  RunOrchestrator.php,readonly final class,"The RunOrchestrator is the message-bus entrypoint for run lifecycle commands and step results, delegating runtime transitions to RunMessageProcessor and dedicated message handlers."
  StartRunHandler.php,readonly final class,The StartRunHandler computes the initial run-start transition and execution effects for start commands.
  ToolCallResultHandler.php,readonly final class,The ToolCallResultHandler collects tool execution outcomes and commits ordered batch results back into run state.